No matter how we resist, history may just repeat itself.
That vessel is so vast... and immeasurable.

That's why we, who merely scurry about within an overly
large vessel...

Regardless of which path we take or how hard we try, we
might end up with the same outcome in the end.
But... even so.

The history that merely repeats itself isn't always filled
with sorrow.

Living in the present doesn't erase the tragedies and
hardships of the past... but it doesn't take away our
ability to move forward or our vision for the future.
Even if it's a blind march... I want to believe that.
Because in our eyes... in my eyes.

Right now, the person I love... is surely looking back at us
with the same feelings.
